sections.content:
The Operator may process the following data:
2.1. Data provided by the User:
Full name;
Email address;
Phone number;
Company details (if provided);
Information provided in questionnaires, forms, and applications.
2.2. Technical data:
IP address;
Device type;
Browser;
Cookies;
Analytics data (Google Analytics, Meta Pixel, etc.).
2.3. Payment data:
The Operator does not store or process bank card data. Payment is made through third-party payment systems (WayForPay, Kaspi, Halyk, etc.).

Personal data is processed for:
Providing access to video materials;
Fulfilling the public offer;
Processing payments;
Communicating with the User;
Sending informational and marketing materials (with consent);
Fraud protection;
Improving the quality of the Site;
Complying with legal requirements.

Processing is carried out on the basis of:
User consent;
Conclusion and performance of a contract;
Legal requirements;
Legitimate interests of the Operator (business protection and fraud prevention).

Processing may be carried out:
Automatically;
Without the use of automation tools.
The Operator has the right to:
Collect;
Systematize;
Store;
Use;
Clarify;
Block;
Delete;
Transfer within the framework of legislation.

The Operator has the right to transfer data to:
Payment services;
Hosting providers;
Email mailing services;
CRM systems;
Government authorities upon lawful request.
Transfer is made in the volume necessary to perform the relevant functions.
The Operator does not sell personal data to third parties.

The Site uses cookies for:
Ensuring proper operation;
Analytics;
Marketing.
The User may disable cookies in their browser settings.

The User has the right to:
Receive information about their data;
Request corrections;
Request deletion (if there are legal grounds);
Withdraw consent to data processing.
Requests should be sent to: reflexcourseai@gmail.com
Processing time ‚Äî up to 15 business days.

The Operator applies reasonable technical and organizational protection measures:
SSL encryption;
Restricted access to data;
Use of secure servers;
Internal access control.
The Operator is not responsible for the actions of third parties who gained access to data due to circumstances beyond the Operator's control.
